Title: Full Stack Developer
Description:
Full Stack Developer
Melbourne CBD | 6 Month Contract from September 2025 | Full-Time
We are seeking a passionate and versatile Full Stack Developer to immediately join our team and play a pivotal role in enhancing Independent Schools Victoria‚Äôs internal software development capabilities. This is an exciting opportunity to contribute to the evolution of our digital platforms and products, supporting the isEducation strategy through innovative and reliable technology solutions. As a key member of the Digital, Data and Technology Team, the Full Stack Developer will collaborate across the organisation to deliver impactful digital experiences, leveraging Microsoft technologies including Dynamics 365 and the Power Platform. The role demands strong technical expertise, a proactive mindset, and a commitment to fostering effective partnerships that drive strategic outcomes.

A supportive and values-driven team environment.
Flexible working arrangements, including hybrid working.

Title: Software Engineer

AWS certification
Why You'll Love Working Here:

Growth:
Opportunities to learn and grow your skills in a dynamic environment.
Autonomy:
We trust you to take ownership and make key decisions.

Ownership:
You'll be building this! It‚Äôs a chance to own the work, not just write code.
The First 12 Months - Setting You Up for Success:

Consistent delivery in every agile sprint cycle
We will have uplifted our capability, quality, robustness, and security!
The Systems are up and running, maintained, and scaled.
You won't need me to hold your hand, you'll have brought new and fresh ideas to the table
Working well with all teams
Important details:
You must possess full, unrestricted working rights for Australia
We are unable to offer visa sponsorship
If you're a talented and passionate software engineer who thrives in collaborative environment, a keen to use technology for good, we encourage you to apply!

Title: Software Engineer
Description:
Great to meet you. We're Energetica, an end-to-end platform for everything to do with enterprise energy and renewables. Buying, selling, analysing, optimising, working towards net zero‚Ä¶ you name it. We do it all, and we do it for some of Australia's biggest names, too!
We're a small (but rapidly growing) team, hyper-focused on building up and scaling our technology both here and globally, and we want smart, focused and hardworking people to join us as we head towards the next stage of our evolution.
Built and managed here in Australia, we are leading the way in technology for the energy and sustainability sector and looking for like-minded individuals who want to roll their sleeves up and get in at the ground floor of an exciting journey.

‚Ä¶ but we don't require you to be:

A great salary appropriate to your experience.
If this all sounds like something you'd be interested in, tell us why and we'd be very happy to hear from you!

Title: Software Developers & Data Engineers (Technical Specialist - Bands 1-3)
Description:
Did you know?
The mission of the Australian Federal Police is to provide dynamic and effective law enforcement to the people of Australia. It provides policing throughout Australia in relation to the prevention and detection of crimes against the Commonwealth, its laws and integrity, and community police services to the Community of the ACT.
Working for the AFP provides you with a diverse and rewarding career. Whether you immerse yourself in a position on the frontline, or provide critical operational or professional support, the work you do makes a big impact on the people of Australia.
We recognise your contribution to our workforce and offer generous remuneration and conditions including:
Six weeks (30 days) of paid annual leave per year + additional paid Christmas stand down
4 extra days of mandatory rest leave per year
18 days of paid personal leave per year
Generous superannuation of 15.4%
18 weeks paid Parental Leave for Primary Caregiver (and 11 weeks for Secondary Caregiver) + additional unpaid leave entitlements for up until 24 months from the child‚Äôs date of birth or placement
Generous salaries and incremental salary progression governed by the AFP Enterprise Agreement
Flexible and hybrid working arrangement that provides work/life balance
Health & wellbeing services ‚Äì with a focus on early intervention, education and prevention
Access to ongoing training and professional development opportunities
What is the role?
Applications are sought from suitably qualified applicants wishing to be considered for the role of Software Developer or Data Engineer.
Digital Surveillance Collection (DSC) develops and operates a wide range of lawful covert surveillance capabilities in support of the AFP‚Äôs operational requirements, including telecommunications interception, surveillance devices, collection under computer access warrant, and collection from open sources.
Our engineering teams manage the collection, ingestion and AI/ML enrichment of structured and unstructured data from diverse sources into analytics platforms, dashboards, reporting tools and operation systems ensuring end-users have access to timely, accurate and actionable insights in support of AFP investigations and intelligence analysis.
You will also be required to contribute to the achievement of outcomes in accordance with the regulatory framework, the AFP Code of Conduct and the AFP Governance Instruments. It is expected that the successful applicant will deliver on the core responsibilities and meet any requirements of the position as outlined below.
For more information about working in Digital Surveillance Collection please visit
https://dscjobs.afp.gov.au.
What will you do?
As a Software Developer or Data Engineer, your responsibilities will include:
Technical Specialist Level 1:
Developing and maintaining applications, data pipelines and ETL processes that enable lawful covert surveillance capabilities and operational data processing for AFP operations.
Collaborating with agile teams to deliver high quality, secure and reliable solutions that meet operation needs while ensuring compliance with applicable legal, regulatory and policy requirements.
Performing research and development of new platforms, processes and technologies to improve operational efficiency and data delivery.
Maintaining up to date technical knowledge and promoting continuous improvement through the application of emerging technologies and engineering best practices.
Technical Specialist Level 2:
Duties as listed under Technical Specialist Level 1, in addition to:
Translating customer requirements into technical solutions, based on a strong understanding of the end-user‚Äôs operating context.
Developing team members and fulfilling a guiding, mentoring and advisory role.
Leading the delivery of day-to-day work, for example, by acting a Scrum Master when required.
Technical Specialist Level 3:
Duties as listed under Technical Specialist Levels 1 and 2, in addition to:
Providing technical leadership for complex bodies of work, including responsibility for delivery in accordance with customer requirements and agreed quality standards.
Proactively driving continuous improvements to technical strategy and architecture, in collaboration with management and peers across the whole of AFP.
Essential Requirements
Technical Specialist Level 1:
You must be an Australian Citizen at the time of application.
Negative Vetting 1 (Secret) security clearance, or the ability to obtain one.
Tertiary qualification or demonstrated experience in related field, such as information technology, data analysis, computer science, software engineering or similar.
Python development skills with hands-on experience in building either data pipelines, front end or backend systems
Demonstrated experience with SQL or NoSQL Databases (e.g. PostgreSQL, Cassandra, Neo4J).
Experience working in a Linux-based development environment.
Experience using collaboration tools that include git, issue tracking and wikis (e.g. GitLab, GitHub, BitBucket, Azure DevOps).
Technical Specialist Level 2:
You must be an Australian Citizen at the time of application.
Negative Vetting 1 (Secret) security clearance, or the ability to obtain one.
Skills and experience as listed under Technical Specialist Level 1, in addition to:
Demonstrated ability to provide technical leadership within a small team and deliver outcomes that meet customer requirements.
Technical Specialist Level 3:
You must be an Australian Citizen at the time of application.
Negative Vetting 1 (Secret) security clearance, or the ability to obtain oneSkills and experience as listed under Technical Specialist Levels 1 and 2, in addition to:
Experience designing architectures and systems with complex integration requirements.
Demonstrated ability in providing strategic technical leadership
Desirable Requirements
While not essential, your application will stand out if you have experience in:
Python web frameworks (e.g. Django, FastAPI, Flask)
Containerisation technologies (e.g. Docker, Kubernetes)
Message queues/event streaming (e.g. Kafka, Apache Pulsar, RabbitMQ/AMQP)
Front-end development (e.g. JavaScript - React, Vue, Alpine, HTML5 and CSS3)
Knowledge and use of CI/CD pipelines
Working with Agile methodologies (e.g. Kanban, Scrum)
No candidate would be expected to have experience in all of these areas, but experience in any of these areas will be highly regarded.
Additional Information
These positions are AFP Technical Specialist - Bands 1-3.
Applicants will be required to undergo a technical assessment.
The selection panel will determine which Technical Specialist level each successful candidate will be placed into.
Commitment to Diversity & Inclusion
At the AFP we value the different perspectives, approaches and lived experiences of our people, and recognise that our collective intelligence and diversity is what makes us stronger. As such, we encourage applications from people from all walks of life, including people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds, First Nations people, women, the LGBTQIA+ community and people with disability.

Title: Growth Engineer (Software Portfolio)
Description:
The Opportunity
We're seeking a hands-on Digital Growth Strategist to accelerate lead generation and digital transformation across our portfolio of B2B software companies. Reporting directly to the CEO, you'll have the autonomy to build and execute digital marketing systems from the ground up, working across two established businesses with a third acquisition planned.
This isn't a role where you'll manage agencies or outsource execution. We need someone who can strategise AND code, someone who gets excited about building marketing automation workflows in the morning and analysing SQL queries in the afternoon. All while working hand in hand with our management team.
About Our Companies
We operate two established B2B Software companies in the automotive software sector - one dominating the Australian/NZ market, the other leading in North America. Together, they serve over 8,000+ users across 4,400+ locations globally.
Both companies are profitable, established market leaders with 30+ years of history, ready for digital acceleration. We're building modern cloud applications that layer on our core platforms, creating opportunities for cross-market innovation and global expansion.
What You'll Actually Do
First 120 Days:
Choose a business segment and completely overhaul its digital acquisition strategy
Build our first marketing automation workflows from scratch
Implement tracking and analytics across the entire funnel
Deploy at least one AI-powered marketing initiative
Establish, present and affirm go-forward strategy and work pipeline
Ongoing Responsibilities:
Write code to connect our platforms (API integrations between websites, CRMs, marketing tools)
Create automated lead nurturing sequences integrated with Salesloft for our sales teams
Develop SEO/content strategies and direct our content resources
Analyse customer data using SQL to identify growth opportunities
Run continuous experiments across both businesses - nothing is steady state here
Work with our SDR and Account teams to create seamless handoffs from marketing to sales
Generate market excitement through intelligent digital orchestration - from geo-targeted campaigns during trade shows and industry events, to SEO dominance and multi-channel lead capture systems that put us wherever our buyers are looking
We have well-established development teams and access to various skills and systems from a code and code governance perspective
What Makes You Perfect for This Role
Technical Skills (Non-Negotiable):
Can write production-ready code (JavaScript, Python, or similar)
Comfortable with APIs and building integrations
SQL proficiency for data analysis
Experience with marketing automation platforms (HubSpot, Marketo, or similar)
HTML/CSS/JavaScript for landing page optimisation
Google Tag Manager and analytics implementation
Experience with AI tools and APIs (OpenAI, Claude CLI, etc.)
Marketing Expertise:
Proven track record of building lead generation systems from zero
Experience with B2B SaaS or software marketing
Understanding of SEO, SEM, and content marketing
Ability to map and optimise customer journeys
Data-driven approach to marketing decisions
The X-Factor:
Growth hacker mentality - you see opportunities where others see obstacles
Comfortable with ambiguity and rapid experimentation
Self-directed learner who stays current with digital trends and AI advancements
Can translate technical capabilities into business outcomes
Excited by the challenge of working across multiple businesses
Forward-thinking about AI's role in marketing - from content generation to predictive analytics
What We Offer
Competitive Salary based on experience¬†and track record, achievement bonus available
True Flexibility: Work remotely or from our Melbourne office (in Brighton)
Direct Impact: Report directly to the CEO with full autonomy over digital strategy
Growth Opportunity: Shape the digital future of multiple businesses, with potential to lead a team
Resources: Access to design service, junior content resource, and budget for tools/platforms
What We DON'T Want:
Someone who will recommend strategies they can't personally implement
Agency managers who outsource the actual work
Traditional marketers uncomfortable with code
People who need constant direction or existing playbooks
Ready to Apply?
We're moving fast on this hire. If you're reading this and thinking "finally, a role where I can build things properly from scratch" - we want to hear from you.
Send your resume and a brief note explaining:
A marketing system you've built from scratch (include technical details)
Your experience working with multiple businesses or brands
A growth hack or automation you're particularly proud of
How you've used or would use AI to solve marketing challenges
We value capability over credentials. Whether you're 19 or 90, if you can deliver results through hands-on execution, we want to talk.
About the Hiring Process:
Initial conversation with our CEO
Technical assessment (bring something to the table to show us)
Paid trial project on one of our businesses
Reference checks and offer
Our companies are part of Constellation Software's portfolio, providing stability and resources while maintaining entrepreneurial freedom. We're building the future of automotive software - come build it with us.
